In this op-ed, President Obama emphasizes the importance of honoring Vietnam veterans on the 50th anniversary of the Vietnam War. He reflects on the sacrifices made by these veterans and acknowledges that they did not always receive the respect they deserved after the war. Obama calls on all Americans to join in honoring and supporting these veterans and their families. He also highlights the efforts being made to ensure that all veterans, including Vietnam veterans, receive the services and support they have earned. Additionally, the President mentions the Joining Forces initiative led by the First Lady and Dr. Jill Biden, which aims to mobilize Americans in supporting military families and veterans. Obama concludes by urging Americans to remember and appreciate all those who have served and sacrificed for the country.